main event: Witness observed a cluster of about a dozen star-like objects in the southeast sky for around 7-8 minutes.
interesting points: The objects appeared brighter than the surrounding stars.
The cluster of lights changed in size as individual lights appeared and disappeared.
The objects remained in the same general area, with the individual lights fading in and out.
The witness compared the appearance of the objects to a cluster of stars in space.
The witness reported the sighting to the Air Force on October 8, 1966.
sighted object: a cluster of about a dozen star-like objects
